  text: Done — I wrote the INDEX/MATCH formulas into cells M6:S11 and saved the result here:

`results/runs/g2b-v8_gpt-4.1_ss-gpt41-fix/eval_GPT54_r1/eval_48983_tc1/output.xlsx`

The formula pattern used is:

`=IFERROR(INDEX($C$6:$I$19, MATCH($L6,$B$6:$B$19,0), MATCH(M$5,$C$5:$I$5,0)), "")`

This lets Excel:
- match the brand from column `L`
- match the category from row `5`
- return the intersecting value from the source table

Then it can be copied across and down through `M6:S11`.
